{"title_page": "List of killings by law enforcement officers in the United States, March 2015", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{List of killings by law enforcement officers in the United States, Description|2015|March}}\n<onlyinclude>\n\n==March 2015==\n<!-- The format adopted is to list killings in reverse chronological order (most recent at top) with date in YYYY-MM-DD format. -->\n<!-- Each entry lists date, name(s) if known, state (city), brief factual description as reported in the media and at least one reference. -->\n<!-- The reference is either 1) a link to a standalone Wikipedia article, -->\n<!-- 2) a direct reference to a reliable source or -->\n<!-- 3) a link to another list in Wikipedia and a direct reference to a reliable source. -->\n<!-- The City location is that as specified by the US Postal Service for the address of the location of the death or for the nearest address to that location. -->\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" id=\"killed\"\n|-\n! Date !! nowrap|Name (Age) of Deceased!!State (City)!!Description<!-- DO NOT OVERWRITE THIS LINE - IT IS THE COLUMN HEADINGS -->\n|-\n| 2015-03-31 || Quezada, Benjamin (21) || [[Baytown, Texas|Texas (Baytown)]] || Baytown Police responded to call just after midnight of a man standing in an intersection with a weapon.  When officers arrived they found Quezada carrying a pellet gun.  He did not drop the weapon as ordered and when he turned pointed it at an officer he was killed with a shotgun.<ref>{{cite web|title=Benjamin Quezada 10295|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/Benjamin-Quezada-10295|website=fatalencounters.org|accessdate=31 October 2016|date=31 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Archer|first1=Phil|title=PD: Man with pellet gun shot dead by Baytown police officer|url=http://www.click2houston.com/news/local/harris-county/pd-man-with-pellet-gun-shot-dead-by-baytown-police-officer|website=click2houston.com|publisher=KPRC 2 Houston, Texas|accessdate=1 November 2016|date=31 March 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|2015-03-31 || Anderson, Jeremy James (36) || [[Tampa, Florida|Florida (Tampa)]] || Anderson was killed by members of a task force of [[United States Marshals Service|United States Marshals]] and Tampa Police who were trying to arrest him on multiple warrants.  Gunfire was exchanged inside the house where Anderson was staying.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jeremy James Anderson 10296|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/Jeremy-James-Anderson-10296|website=fatalencounters.org|accessdate=31 October 2016|date=31 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Sullivan|first1=Dan|last2=Mettler|first2=Katie|title=Man shot dead as U.S. Marshals serve warrant at Carrollwood home|url=http://www.tampabay.com/news/publicsafety/crime/man-shot-as-tampa-police-marshals-office-serve-search-warrant/2223666|website=tampabay.com|publisher=Tampa Bay Times, St. Petersburg, Florida|accessdate=1 November 2016|date=1 April 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| nowrap|2015-03-31 || White, Philip (32) || [[Vineland, New Jersey|New Jersey (Vineland)]] || Residents on the 100 block of Grape Street called police after seeing a man acting strange on the sidewalk. When officers Louis Platania and Richard Janasiak responded to the disorderly conduct call, the situation escalated and 32-year-old Philip White was arrested then taken to the hospital in 'respiratory distress' where he was pronounced dead. In the days following the incident, a video from an eye-witness emerged showing one of the officers on Mr White's back before a police dog is called over. The Officers allow the dog to attack Mr White while the officer on his back continues to punch. The dog is allowed to maul the unconscious body of Mr White, biting and tearing several times on his head, neck and arms while he lay in the road. The video did not show how Mr White came to be in the road.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://6abc.com/news/new-video-obtained-in-vineland-police-custody-death/639341/|title=New video obtained in Vineland police custody death|work=6abc Philadelphia|accessdate=21 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/video.php?v=973999825944263|title=Graphic New Video Backs Up Witness... - Charlottecountyflcopwatch - Facebook|work=facebook.com|accessdate=21 April 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-30 || Babb, Brian (49) || [[Eugene, Oregon|Oregon (Eugene)]] || The therapist of a troubled veteran called 911.  Officers responded by driving an armored vehicle onto his property.  Babb allegedly shouldered an unloaded rifle and officers shot the man dead.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kmtr.com/news/local/KMTR-Family-of-veteran-shot-and-killed-by-police-calls-for-change-302490301.html|title=Family of veteran shot and killed by police calls for change|date=4 May 2015|work=KMTR|accessdate=8 May 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-30 || Wise, Dominick R. (30) || [[Culpeper, Virginia|Virginia (Culpeper)]] || Culpeper Police responded to reports of a man walking in circles in the middle of the street.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dominick R. Wise 10290|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/Dominick-R.-Wise-10290|website=fatalencounters.org|accessdate=31 October 2016|date=30 March 2015}}</ref> When an officer talked to him he fled.  He was tased more than once and several officers subdued him and put him in handcuffs.  After paramedics arrived he became unresponsive and soon died at a hospital.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Johnston|first1=Donnie|title=Culpeper man dies after being Tasered by police|url=http://www.fredericksburg.com/news/crime_courts/culpeper-man-dies-after-being-tasered-by-police/article_46debc2a-d727-11e4-a18f-5b06a6f5b1bd.html|website=fredericksburg.com|publisher=The Free Lance-Star, Fredericksburg, Virginia|accessdate=2 November 2016|date=30 March 2015}}</ref> The Medical Examiner in Manasas, Virginia attributed the accidental death to heart arrhythmia due to PCP intoxication, restraint and exertion, and the taser.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Champion|first1=Allison Brophy|title=Medical examiner: Taser, PCP, heart arrhythmia led to death of Culpeper man in police custody|url=http://www.dailyprogress.com/starexponent/medical-examiner-taser-pcp-heart-arrhythmia-led-to-accidental-death/article_af08fae8-13ab-11e5-803e-1b2e4338cb83.html|website=dailprogress.com|publisher=Culpeper Star-Exponent|accessdate=7 November 2016|date=15 June 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-30 || Hall, Ricky \"Mya\" Shawatza (27) || [[Fort Meade, Maryland|Maryland (Fort Meade)]] || Hall and a companion Fleming were driving an SUV they had recently stolen from a third companion.  In an apparent error of navigation, they took an exit restricted to [[National Security Agency|NSA]] employees but refused police commands to stop, possibly because they had drugs inside the vehicle.  Police fired on the vehicle, which then crashed into a cruiser.  Hall died at the scene.<ref>{{cite news|title=A fatal wrong turn suspected at NSA|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/crime/officials-respond-to-incident-at-nsa-on-fort-meade-campus/2015/03/30/08bdfe56-d6e1-11e4-ba28-f2a685dc7f89_story.html|accessdate=13 May 2015|work=The Washington Post|date=March 30, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=FBI identifies man who died in NSA incident as Ricky Shawatza Hall|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/crime/fbi-identifies-man-who-died-in-nsa-incident-as-ricky-shawatza-hall/2015/03/31/d10e87d6-d7b3-11e4-8103-fa84725dbf9d_story.html|accessdate=13 May 2015|work=The Washington Post|date=March 31, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mic.com/articles/117228/black-women-continue-getting-killed-by-police-why-aren-t-more-people-discussing-it|title=Black Women Are Getting Killed by Police, Too \u2014 So Why Aren't More People Discussing It?|author= Derrick Clifton|date=30 March 2015|work=Identities.Mic|accessdate=13 May 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-29 || Moland, Jason (29) || [[Modesto, California|California (Modesto)]] || An off-duty police officer and a woman were at a park when they were approached by Mr. Moland, and a confrontation ensued. Mr. Moland brandished a weapon, and the officer shot him. Later the brandished weapon was identified as a BB gun.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news10.net/story/news/local/modesto/2015/03/30/ceres-officer-fatal-shooting/70660046/|title=Off-duty Ceres police officer involved in fatal shooting|author=Hayley Guenthner, News10 Staff|date=30 March 2015|work=NEWS10|accessdate=21 April 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-29 || Allen, John Marcel (54) || [[Boulder City, Nevada|Nevada (Boulder City)]] || Boulder City Police officers, responding to a call of shots fired, encountered Allen outside his apartment building.  When he shot at them police returned fire, killing him.<ref>{{cite web|title=John Marcell Allen|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/John-Marcell-Allen-10289|website=fatalencounters.org|accessdate=31 October 2016|date=29 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Lochhead|first1=Colton|title=Man shot, killed by Boulder City police|url=http://www.reviewjournal.com/news/nevada/man-shot-killed-boulder-city-police|website=reviewjournal.com|publisher=Las Vegas Review-Journal|accessdate=2 November 2016|date=30 March 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-29 || Herbert, Byron (29) || [[Elizabethtown, Kentucky|Kentucky (Elizabethtown)]] || Responding to a disturbance at a store parking lot, an officer confronted Mr. Herbert who was assaulting a woman and brandishing a handgun. Gunfire was exchanged and the suspect was fatally shot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wave3.com/story/28651475/man-in-officer-involved-shooting-dies|title=Suspect shot by Elizabethtown officer identified|author=Charles Gazaway|date=30 March 2015|work=wave3.com|accessdate=21 April 2015}}</ref> \n|-\n| 2015-03-28 || Rooker, Robert (26) || [[Latham, Ohio|Ohio (Latham)]] || Pike County Sheriff Deputies attempted to pull over Rooker for speeding.<ref>{{cite web|title=Robert Rooker 10284|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/Robert-Rooker-10284|website=fatalencounters.org|accessdate=31 October 2016|date=28 March 2015}}</ref> Deputies say that when Rooker used his vehicle to ram and to attempt to ram their cars, they shot and killed him.<ref>{{cite web|last1=LaGrand|first1=Chris|title=Pike County Sheriff's Deputies Shoot And Kill Man After Vehicle Chase|url=http://www.10tv.com/article/pike-county-sheriffs-deputies-shoot-and-kill-man-after-vehicle-chase|website=10tv.com|publisher=WBNS-10TV, Columbus, Ohio|accessdate=2 November 2016|date=30 March 2015}}</ref> Deputy Joel Jenkins was indicted for manslaughter and reckless homicide.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ex-deputy surrenders after charges filed in 2 Ohio killings, one while on-duty|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/nationworld/midwest/ct-fatal-shootings-former-ohio-deputy-charged-20151211-story.html|website=chicagotribune.com|publisher=Chicago Tribune|accessdate=2 November 2016|date=11 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Nealeigh|first1=Sara|title=Jenkins, Pike Co. Sheriff's Office face federal lawsuit|url=http://www.chillicothegazette.com/story/news/local/2016/08/01/jenkins-pike-co-sheriffs-office-federal-lawsuit/87914962/|website=chillicothegazette.com|publisher=Chillicothe Gazette|accessdate=6 November 2016|date=3 August 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-28 || Hockaday, Meagan (26) || [[Oxnard, California|California (Oxnard)]] || Responding to a 911 call of a domestic dispute, two Oxnard police officers went to an apartment about 1 a.m. While an officer was talking with Hokaday's boyfriend, who had made the call, Hockaday approached the two with a knife.  The officer shot and killed Hockaday.<ref>{{cite web|title=Meagan Hockaday (10285)|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/Meagan-Hockaday-10285|website=Fatalencounters.org|accessdate=21 August 2016|date=28 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Leung|first1=Wendy|title=Oxnard woman killed by police after domestic dispute call|url=http://www.vcstar.com/news/local/oxnard/oxnard-woman-killed-by-police-after-domestic-dispute-call-ep-1012501557-347065802.html|website=vcstar.com|publisher=Ventura County Star|accessdate=21 August 2016|date=29 March 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-27 || Kendrick, Gary (56) || [[Encinitas, California|California (Encinitas)]] || A 56-year-old Encinitas man was shot and killed by a San Diego County sheriff's deputy Friday.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utsandiego.com/news/2015/mar/30/gary-kendrick-shot-encinitas-sheriffs-deputy/|title=Gary Kendrick identified as man killed by sheriff's deputy - UTSanDiego.com|author=Teri Figueroa|work=U-T San Diego|accessdate=21 April 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-27 || Hernandez, Adrian (23) || [[Bakersfield, California|California (Bakersfield)]] || A crime-spree-filled day ended in a police shoot-out in which Hernandez was killed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kerngoldenempire.com/story/d/story/man-killed-in-officer-involved-shooting-identified/35304/cRubG_UnF0uwaO5hUaDX2w|title=Man killed in officer involved shooting identified|author=Associated Press|work=KernGoldenEmpire|accessdate=21 April 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150801043417/http://www.kerngoldenempire.com/story/d/story/man-killed-in-officer-involved-shooting-identified/35304/cRubG_UnF0uwaO5hUaDX2w|archive-date=1 August 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Calahan|first1=Tim|last2=Santiago|first2=Brandon|last3=Shaterian|first3=Crosby|title=Adrian Hernandez, 22, rape and arson suspect, killed in shootout near Garces High School|url=http://www.turnto23.com/news/local-news/pursuit-ends-in-gunfire-near-garces-high-school|website=TurnTo23.com|publisher=Scripps TV Station Group|accessdate=August 9, 2016|date=March 27, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-27 || Pope, Aaron (34)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.toledoblade.com/Editorials/2015/04/01/Cops-under-scrutiny-1.html|title=Cops under scrutiny|work=Toledo Blade|accessdate=21 April 2015}}</ref> || [[Toledo, Ohio|Ohio (Toledo)]] || Police responded to a call of Pope acting out of control. Family members said police used too much force when they were detaining the unarmed man, by putting pressure on his chest including an officer holding him down with his knees. Police did not call for an ambulance but transported Pope to the hospital themselves, where he was pronounced dead.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.toledoblade.com/Police-Fire/2015/03/30/Family-of-Toledo-man-who-died-in-police-custody-seek-answers.html|title=Family of Toledo man who died in police custody seeks answers|work=Toledo Blade|accessdate=21 April 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-27 || Oates, Harvey E. (42) || [[Fort Ashby, West Virginia|West Virginia (Fort Ashby)]] || West Virginia State Troopers received a call about a distraught man in possession of a gun.  When an officer attempted a traffic stop the suspect fled his vehicle and ran into the woods with his gun, threatening to shoot officers and himself.  After a ninety-minute standoff Oates moved toward the officers and pointed his gun at them.  A trooper shot and killed him.<ref>{{cite web|title=Harvey E. Oates 10283|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/Harvey-E.-Oates-10283|website=fatalencounters.org|accessdate=31 October 2016|date=27 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Armed suspect fatally shot by trooper in Mineral County after pursuit, standoff|url=http://www.times-news.com/news/armed-suspect-fatally-shot-by-trooper-in-mineral-county-after/article_b19ddc8a-d565-11e4-8511-9bae0bf78ac8.html|website=times-news.com|publisher=Cumberland (Maryland) Times-News|accessdate=2 November 2016|date=28 March 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-27 || Hall, Jamalis (39) || [[Fort Pierce, Florida|Florida (Fort Pierce)]] || Hall was wanted on a murder warrant when he was pulled over by a task force including officers from St. Lucie County Sheriff's office.  He was lying on the floor of the van and when he reached for a knife he was shot and killed.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jamalis Hall 10280|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/Jamalis-Hall-10280|website=fatalencounters.org|accessdate=31 October 2016|date=27 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Sparks|first1=John|last2=Hackett|first2=Jason|title=St. Lucie Co. deputy shoots, kills armed suspect, sheriff's office says|url=http://www.wptv.com/news/region-st-lucie-county/fort-pierce/officer-involved-shooting-in-fort-pierce|website=wptv.com|publisher=WPTV, West Palm Beach, Florida|accessdate=2 November 2016|date=27 March 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-27 || Seifert, Neil J. (40) || [[Webster, Massachusetts|Massachusetts (Webster)]] || Webster Police responding to a domestic disturbance call learned that Seifert had left the scene in his girlfriend's car.  When he returned to his girlfriend's home he had a shotgun which he fired at police.  They returned fire, killing him.<ref>{{cite web|title=Neil J. Seifert 10279|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/Neil-J.-Seifert-10279|website=fatalencounters.org|accessdate=31 October 2016|date=27 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Crimaldi|first1=Laura|last2=Pattani|first2=Aneri|title=Police shoot and kill man armed with shotgun in Webster|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2015/03/27/police-shoot-and-kill-armed-man-webster/w0FWTX6bS7arg07egXh7LP/story.html|website=bostonglobe.com|publisher=Boston Globe|accessdate=2 November 2016|date=27 March 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-27 || West, Angelo (41) || [[Roxbury, Massachusetts|Massachusetts (Roxbury)]] || Boston Police [[Gang intelligence unit|gang unit officers]] investigating a report of shots fired pulled over a vehicle carrying three men.  The suspect stepped out of the car and fled, firing his gun at the officers.  One officer was shot in the face.  The other officers returned fire, killing Angelo West.  The wounded officer was in critical condition at a hospital.<ref>{{cite web|title=Angelo West 10281|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/Angelo-West-10281|website=fatalencounters.org|accessdate=31 October 2016|date=27 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Fox|first1=Jeremy C.|last2=Hanson|first2=Melissa|last3=Allen|first3=Evan|title=Moynihan helped save life of officer in Watertown shootout|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2015/03/27/police-officer-shot-roxbury/yVrrI7dn3BeT8iWX9wKL3M/story.html|website=bostonglobe.com|publisher=Boston Globe|accessdate=2 November 2016|date=27 March 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-26 || Solis, Adrian (35) || [[Los Angeles, California|California (Los Angeles)]] || Two Los Angeles Police officers responded to a call of a suicidal man in the [[Wilmington, Los Angeles|Wilmington]] neighborhood. They arrived to find a man bleeding from a deep cut in his neck.  When the paramedics arrived, one officer went outside to direct them, leaving one officer with the subject.  Solis jumped up, grabbed two kitchen knives, and approached the officer who had remained.  The officer went outside, followed by Solis who continued to advance.  An officer shot and killed Solis.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adrian Solis 10275|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/Adrian-Solis-10275|website=fatalencounters.org|accessdate=24 September 2016|date=26 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Marantos|first1=Jeanette|title=Adrian Gustavo Solis, 35|url=http://homicide.latimes.com/post/adrian-gustavo-solis/|website=homicide.latimes.com|publisher=Los Angeles Times|accessdate=24 September 2016|date=15 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Suspect Charges Officers and Paramedics with Knife|url=http://lapdblog.typepad.com/lapd_blog/2015/04/page/6/|website=lapdblog.typepad.com|publisher=Los Angeles Police Department|accessdate=24 September 2016|date=7 April 2015}}</ref>   \n|-\n| 2015-03-26 || Choate, Deanne (53) || [[Gardner, Kansas|Kansas (Gardner)]] || Police were called to a home by a man who said a woman had discharged a handgun inside the home.  When they arrived the woman was in bed.  The two officers handcuffed the man and put him into their car.  They then went into the room and within a few minutes the man heard several gunshots.  The officers had shot and killed the woman.<ref>{{cite web|title=Deanne Choate 10276|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/Deanne-Choate-10276|website=fatalencounters.org|accessdate=31 October 2016|date=26 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Officer-involved shooting in Gardner, Kan., leaves 1 woman dead, 2 officers on administrative leave|url=http://www.kshb.com/news/local-news/officer-involved-shooting-in-gardner-kan-leaves-1-woman-dead-2-officers-on-administrative-leave|website=kshb.com|publisher=KSHB 41, Kansas City, Missouri|accessdate=2 November 2016|date=28 March 2015}}</ref> Johnson County District Attorney decided that the officers were justified in shooting the woman.<ref>{{cite web|title=Boyfriend speaks out about police shooting that killed woman|url=http://www.cbs46.com/story/29422985/boyfriend-speaks-out-about-police-shooting-that-killed-woman|website=cbs46.com|publisher=WGCL-TV, CBS 46, Atlanta, Georgia|accessdate=2 November 2016|date=27 July 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-26 || Smith, Gregory Thomas Joseph (39) || [[Crown Point, Indiana|Indiana (Crown Point)]] || Smith was being transferred between areas of the Lake County Jail when he had an outburst.  Officers used a taser to stun him and he went into cardiac arrest.  He was pronounced dead at a hospital.<ref>{{cite web|title=Thomas Joseph Smith 10274|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/Gregory-Thomas-Joseph-Smith-10274|website=fatalencounters|accessdate=31 October 2016|date=26 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Reese|first1=Sarah|title=Family sues after Hobart man dies while being held at Lake County Jail|url=http://www.nwitimes.com/news/local/lake/family-sues-after-hobart-man-dies-while-being-held-at/article_5585fdf9-368d-5e13-9e00-706dcff9a038.html|website=nwitimes.com|publisher=Times Media Company, Munster, Indiana|accessdate=1 November 2016|date=1 April 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-25 || Terrazas, Victor Daniel (28) || [[Los Angeles, California|California (Los Angeles)]] || Los Angeles County Sh