all reporting an armed man was threatening him.  Sizer told the 911 operator he was armed to protect himself.  When police arrived Sizer was outside his home.  Officers told him to get on the ground and when he said he could not, they tased him.  As he fell to the ground he struck his head, causing a large cut.  He was taken for medical treatment, then to jail, and released the next day.  He died March 14.  The family claims his death was caused by the injury to his head and has filed a lawsuit.<ref>{{cite web|title=Family claims North Austin man's death due to APD excessive force|url=http://keyetv.com/news/local/family-claims-north-austin-mans-death-due-to-apd-excessive-force|website=keyetv.com|publisher=KEYE TV, Austin, Texas|accessdate=26 October 2016|date=16 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Jankowski|first1=Philip|title=Lawsuit reveals unreported death after Austin police stunned man|url=http://www.mystatesman.com/news/news/local/lawsuit-reveals-unreported-death-after-austin-poli/npkS3/|website=mystatesman.com|publisher=Austin American-Statesman|accessdate=26 October 2016|date=15 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-06 || Vinzant, Naeschylus (37) || [[Aurora, Colorado|Colorado (Aurora)]] || Vinzant, walking in a street unarmed, was shot once in the chest by an Aurora police officer. He was wanted for a parole violation when an officer approached him. It has not been determined what prompted the officer to fire.<ref>[http://www.denverpost.com/news/ci_27947831/still-no-answers-fatal-shooting-by-aurora-police Still no answers in fatal shooting by Aurora police], [[Denver Post]], April 20, 2015.</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-05 || Hubbard, Tyson (34) || [[Lincoln, Nebraska|Nebraska (Lincoln)]] || Tyson Hubbard, wanted for allegedly breaking a man's eye socket with a drill, was shot and killed after struggling with a Lincoln Police officer and Lancaster County Sheriff deputy who attempted to arrest Hubbard on the driver's side of his vehicle.  A U.S. marshal, approa