ale, Arizona|Arizona (Glendale)]] || After allegedly brandishing a firearm in a verbal exchange with a couple at an ATM, Tassinari was traced to his home and confronted by police. He allegedly reached for a weapon in his waistband and was both tazered and then shot dead by an officer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.azcentral.com/story/news/local/glendale/2015/03/25/glendale-officer-involved-shooting-one-injured-abrk/70415468/|title=1 dead in Glendale officer-involved shooting|date=25 March 2015|work=azcentral|accessdate=21 April 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-24 || Dunham, Scott (57) || [[San Jose, California|California (San Jose)]] || Three officers responded to a call of a threatening incident at Dunham's apartment. Upon approaching the building, Dunham opened fire killing one officer. Return gunfire killed Dunham on his balcony.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mercurynews.com/crime-courts/ci_27793496/san-jose-police-officers-return-fire-fatally-wounded|title=San Jose police: Officer's return fire fatally wounded gunman who killed cop|work=mercurynews.com|accessdate=21 April 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-24 ||  Snyder, Steven T. (36) || [[Fond du Lac, Wisconsin|Wisconsin (Fond du Lac)]] ||Snyder, suspected of a bank robbery, was apparently shot and killed in a shootout with State Troooper Trevor Casper (21).  Snyder's shots also killed Trooper Casper in the exchange of gunfire.<ref>{{cite web|title=Steven T. Snyder 10268|url=http://data.fatalencounters.org/page/Steven-T.-Snyder-10268|website=fatalencounters.org|accessdate=31 October 2016|date=24 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Jones|first1=Meg|last2=Spicuzza|first2=Mary|last3=Glauber|first3=Bill|title=Law enforcement piecing together robbery, killing, shootout|url=http://archive.jsonline.com/news/crime/3-dead-including-trooper-after-trail-of-violence-ends-in-fond-du-lac-b99468884z1-297498871.html|website=jsonline.com|publisher=Journal-Sentinel, Milwaukee, Wisconsin|accessdate=1 November 2016|date=25 March 2015}}<