t man during drug arrest Friday night|url=http://www.gainesville.com/news/20150309/putnam-deputies-fatally-shot-man-during-drug-arrest-friday-night|website=gainesville.com|publisher=Gainesville Sun|accessdate=26 October 2016|date=9 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Scanlan|first1=Dan|title=Putnam County man shot and killed by deputies during Friday night drug sting|url=http://jacksonville.com/news/crime/2015-03-09/story/putnam-county-man-shot-and-killed-deputies-during-friday-night-drug|website=jacksonville.com|publisher=Florida Times-Union|accessdate=26 October 2016|date=9 March 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-06 || Moore, Bernard (??) || [[Atlanta|Georgia (Atlanta)]] || Moore was crossing the street to get back to work when he was fatally struck by an allegedly speeding police cruiser.  Officer Christopher Blaise, the driver, was not responding to any emergency at the time and did not have emergency lights or sirens.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Shropshire|first1=Terry |title=Family of Bernard Moore, who was killed by police car, to plea at City Hall|url=http://chicagodefender.com/2015/05/12/family-of-bernard-moore-who-was-killed-by-police-car-to-plea-at-city-hall/|work=Chicago Defender|date=May 12, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-06 || Robinson, Anthony (19) || [[Madison, Wisconsin|Wisconsin (Madison)]] || [[Shooting of Tony Robinson]]. According to Madison police chief Michael Koval, police received calls for a man jumping in and out of traffic and committing battery.  Police officer Matthew Kenny followed Robinson into an apartment, where Robinson allegedly assaulted the officer, who then shot him multiple times.  Robinson was unarmed.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Southall|first1=Ashley|title=Man Shot Dead by Police After Scuffle in Wisconsin|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/08/us/man-shot-dead-by-police-after-scuffle-in-wisconsin.html|accessdate=7 March 2015|work=New York Times}}</ref> The prosecutor concluded that this was a lawful use of deadly force and Kenny was not charged with any crime, though a civil lawsuit from the family is pending.<ref>{{cite news|title=Prosecutor: No charges for officer in Tony Robinson case|url=http://www.cnn.com/2015/05/12/us/tony-robinson-madison-killing-investigation/|accessdate=15 May 2015|work=CNN}}</ref> Details from the investigation have been publicly released.<ref>http://www.doj.state.wi.us/dci/officer-involved-critical-incident</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-06 || Sizer, James Fred (62) || [[Austin, Texas|Texas (Austin)]] || Austin Police officers responded to Sizer's call reporting a armed man was threatening him.  Sizer told the 911 operator he was armed to protect himself.  When police arrived Sizer was outside his home.  Officers told him to get on the ground and when he said he could not, they tased him.  As he fell to the ground he struck his head, causing a large cut.  He was taken for medical treatment, then to jail, and released the next day.  He died March 14.  The family claims his death was caused by the injury to his head and has filed a lawsuit.<ref>{{cite web|title=Family claims North Austin man's death due to APD excessive force|url=http://keyetv.com/news/local/family-claims-north-austin-mans-death-due-to-apd-excessive-force|website=keyetv.com|publisher=KEYE TV, Austin, Texas|accessdate=26 October 2016|date=16 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Jankowski|first1=Philip|title=Lawsuit reveals unreported death after Austin police stunned man|url=http://www.mystatesman.com/news/news/local/lawsuit-reveals-unreported-death-after-austin-poli/npkS3/|website=mystatesman.com|publisher=Austin American-Statesman|accessdate=26 October 2016|date=15 December 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015-03-06 || Vinzant, Naeschylus (37) || [[Aurora, Colorado|Colorado (Aurora)]] || Vinzant, walking in a street unarmed, was shot once in the chest by an Aurora police officer. He was wanted for a parole violation when an officer approached him. It has not been determined what prompted the officer to fire.<ref>[http://ww